#!/usr/bin/env bash
# memory-cli — discoverability wrapper for the Graphiti memory client
#
# Why this exists
# ---------------
# All Builder agent instructions reference `/skills/scripts/memory-cli`, but no
# binary has ever existed at that path inside agent runtime containers. The
# real CLI ships under the `tool--memory` skill. Without this wrapper, every
# agent's session-open `search-facts` call fails silently and the
# knowledge-graph layer of CableSnap is invisible.
#
# This wrapper:
#   1. Probes the known canonical locations of the real memory-cli.
#   2. Execs the first one found, forwarding all args.
#   3. Prints a single, actionable error if nothing is found — so future
#      agents see "fix your container" rather than "memory store is broken."
#
# See BLD-746 for the full diagnosis. Once the host bind-mount adds
# /skills/scripts/memory-cli, this wrapper can stay as a lightweight shim
# (it's idempotent — the first found path wins) or be removed.
#
# Usage:
#   scripts/memory-cli search-facts "query" main
#   scripts/memory-cli search-nodes "query" main
#   scripts/memory-cli add "Decision Name" "Body details" main "source"

set -euo pipefail

CANDIDATES=(
  # Direct skill source — most reliable, present in every container today.
  "/skills/claude-skills/tool--memory/scripts/memory-cli"
  # Hashed symlink under the agent home, also points at the same source.
  "${HOME:-/paperclip}/.claude/skills/tool-memory--b85488da58/scripts/memory-cli"
  # Documented (but currently non-existent) double-dash variant — kept so
  # this wrapper keeps working if someone normalizes the symlink name.
  "${HOME:-/paperclip}/.claude/skills/tool--memory/scripts/memory-cli"
  # Hypothetical future host-side fix for BLD-746.
  "/skills/scripts/memory-cli"
)

for cli in "${CANDIDATES[@]}"; do
  if [[ -x "$cli" ]]; then
    exec "$cli" "$@"
  fi
done

cat >&2 <<'ERR'
memory-cli: no working memory-cli binary found on this container.

Searched (in order):
  - /skills/claude-skills/tool--memory/scripts/memory-cli
  - $HOME/.claude/skills/tool-memory--b85488da58/scripts/memory-cli
  - $HOME/.claude/skills/tool--memory/scripts/memory-cli
  - /skills/scripts/memory-cli

This means the tool--memory skill is not mounted in this container.
File the gap on BLD-746 (or its successor) — do NOT silently skip the
memory step. Inline-curate to the Paperclip issue thread as a stopgap.
ERR
exit 127
